text.section:
The commissioner may take possession and close a bank for purposes of liquidation in any case in which the commissioner finds that the bank:
Is insolvent;
Has permitted capital to become impaired to a level which does not permit the bank to operate in a safe and sound manner;
Has had insurance of depositors' accounts terminated by the FDIC; or
Has requested through its board of directors that the commissioner take possession for the benefit of depositors, other creditors and shareholders.
